               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ADOLPHUS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1286" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1286" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1286" type="surname" value="FLOWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1286" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY FLOWER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am managing clerk to Messrs, Goding and Co., brewers, in Belvedere-road, Lambeth. Ball was employed about their premises in Nov. last—he was to wait on the clerks, and go on errands or messages for them—in Nov. last I had a 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note of my own, which I put into a drawer in the strong closet in the brewery—Ball bad access to that closet—the key of the drawer was on a bunch of keys which was in the closet—I missed the note on my return from Dover, about the 20th of Nov.—it had been safe two or three days before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1287" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1287" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1287" type="surname" value="FENNING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1287" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT FENNING</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 181.) On the 24th of Feb. I went to Goding's brewery—I saw Ball—Mr. Goding sent for him to the counting-house—I cautioned him not to say anything, and I said I was to take him for some other things—I named the, 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note—he said he bad not taken it—he afterwards said something, and I fetched Harvey to the station—Harvey said in Ball's presence that Ball had taken a 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note and brought it to Lewis—Ball denied it—Harvey said, "You know you brought the 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note and another note, and received 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. for it, you may as well tell the truth, for I shall"—nothing further passed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1288" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1288" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1288" type="surname" value="PERRY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1288" type="given" value="JOHN PETER"></interp>JOHN PETER PERRY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk at Lambeth Police-court. When Ball was brought up for examination he said, (<hi rend="italic">reading</hi>) "What he says (meaning Harvey) is right; they gave me 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. for the 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. and 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. notes, but asked me for 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. back, because they said they could not change the 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note."Harvey says," When Ball came for the 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. I was there; he told me that he had a 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note and a 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note, and sold them for 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Ball.</hi> James Halnut came up with Harvey, and told me to say what Harvey said, but what Harvey said was not true.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1289" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1289" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1289" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1289" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HARVEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am fourteen years old. I was in the service of Edward and Samuel Lewis till they were taken into custody—I know Pall quite well—I have seen him at Lewis's lodgings, at No. 3, Artichoke-court, Lambeth—I have seen Ball there in a morning, and the Lewis's were up in a corner whispering about notes, and in going up the Cut one night Ball said to me, "I sold Samuel Lewis a 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note and a 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note for 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and be made me give him 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. back, he said there was one note bad, and he could not change it"—I heard the Lewis's say up in the room that Ball had got a 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note and a 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note, and "I will take them to Bill to change them"—Edward and Samuel Lewis both said that—Samuel Lewis sent me one night to Ball to get some money—he told me to tell Bali that Edward was ill, and he wanted some money—Ball told me he got the notes from Mr. Goding's brewery, and another thing he told me that he took a check off Mr. Goding's table, and he said it was a g-s shame that the Lewis only gave him 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. for the notes, and made him give them 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Samuel Lewis. Q.</hi> Did you ever see Ball give me a 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. note? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, but you and Edward Lewis went up in a corner and whispered about notes—I used to see Ball at your place very often—you was not at work at Mr. Starling's when Ball came up—you did not work at Mr. Starling's while I was with you, which was eight, or nine, or ten week-Ball tow me he brought the notes one day—you, and I, and Edward Lewis were there when Ball came up—you called him in the corner, and whispered to</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184504070220"></xptr>
               <p>him—we had not long got up—he brought a basket, and put it down by the window.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Samuel Lewis.</hi> I never had the notes—I worked at Mr. Starling's from the 11th of Nov. till after Christmas—my brother told me that Harvey had been at Union-hall. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I never was taken up in my life for anything.</p>
               <p>
